-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Aug 29
-- 
-- Fri Aug 29, 2014 03:33AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Aug 29 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Friday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- The consultative council on Corporate Commercial Bank (Corpbank) <6C9.BB>, a Bulgarian business representatives' group which was established earlier this month, has proposed a list of measures to rescue the troubled lender without burden to taxpayers (Trud, Capital daily). PRESA - Bulgaria's central bank would reopen Corpbank only if investors propose 6 billion levs for the rehabilitation of the troubled lender, sources familiar with the process, said.   -- Bulgaria's former Prime Minister Ivan Kostov said that negotiations with this potential investor should be launched immediately to allow the Corpbank to resume work without a bailout package from the government and the central bank (Sega, Presa). -- Bulgaria will seek assistance from the European Commission for direct damages worth five to 10 million levs (6.73 million US dollar) caused by the Russian food embargo, Interim Agriculture Minister Vasil Grudev said, adding the damage estimate had been calculated on the basis of contracts for certain types of products which would not be fulfilled (Standart, Presa, Monitor, Capital daily, Duma). -- Interim Labour Minister Yordan Hristoskov has suggested that a minimum monthly wage hike from 340 levs to 400 levs will not harm the business sector (Standart, Sega, Monitor, Duma).